Mecklenburg
County Board of Commissioners.

04:22.662 --> 04:27.634 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's been out in the Charlotte
community today,
and I spoke with him a short
time ago.

04:27.667 --> 04:29.669 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Chairman Fuller, thank you for
joining us.

04:29.703 --> 04:32.639 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How would you describe the
situation in Charlotte
right now?

04:32.672 --> 04:34.908 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TREVOR FULLER, Chairman,
Mecklenburg County
Board of Commissioners: Well,
there's no doubt

04:34.941 --> 04:36.610 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that it's very tense.

04:36.643 --> 04:38.712 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Thank you for having me, Judy.

04:38.745 --> 04:46.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a tense time in Mecklenburg
County, something
we haven't really seen in our
lifetimes.

04:46.953 --> 04:52.559 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so we are trying our best to
keep things
under control as best we can.

04:52.592 --> 04:55.862 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What are you
hearing from people
you talk to in the community?

04:55.896 --> 05:01.368 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we should say Mecklenburg
County essentially
encircles the city of Charlotte.

05:01.401 --> 05:03.236 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TREVOR FULLER: That's right.

05:03.270 --> 05:08.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, Mecklenburg County, we have
over a million
people who live here,
approximately 800,000

05:08.308 --> 05:11.478 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of whom live in the city of
Charlotte.

05:11.511 --> 05:19.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what we're hearing is a high
degree of
unrest, uncertainty about what's
going to

05:19.419 --> 05:22.556 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
happen tonight and the next
several days.

05:22.589 --> 05:30.230 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so what we're trying to do
is to manage
-- manage the flow of
information, to manage

05:30.263 --> 05:35.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our emotional state, and hoping
that we can
get some calm, so that we can
then have the

05:35.869 --> 05:37.637 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
dialogue that we so desperately
need.

05:37.671 --> 05:42.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Do you think it
was the right
decision to bring in the
National Guard to

05:42.042 --> 05:45.445 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
beef up, in effect, the police
tonight?

05:45.478 --> 05:52.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TREVOR FULLER: Well, it's clear
that we didn't
have enough resources last
night, and so I

05:52.686 --> 05:57.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
felt it was necessary for us to
have some
additional resources available
to us.

05:57.791 --> 06:02.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even if it's more than we need,
I think we're
better off having the greater
resources than

06:02.762 --> 06:04.531 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
not.

06:04.564 --> 06:08.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What sort of job
do you believe
the leaders in the community
have done so

06:08.535 --> 06:10.637 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
far, the police chief, the
mayor, and others?

06:10.670 --> 06:18.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TREVOR FULLER: Well, I think
everyone is working
just as hard as they can to try
to deal with

06:19.012 --> 06:22.582 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the situation that really we
haven't dealt
with in our community.

06:22.616 --> 06:26.519 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have had big events here, but
nothing quite
like this.

06:26.553 --> 06:33.693 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And so I'm a little more
forgiving under circumstances
that people haven't dealt with
before.

06:33.727 --> 06:40.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think we're doing the best we
can, in particular
our chief of police, who is
trying hard under

06:40.166 --> 06:43.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
very difficult circumstances to
maintain control.

06:43.570 --> 06:47.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What do you mean
when you say
this is something the community
has not dealt

06:47.140 --> 06:48.908 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with before?

06:48.942 --> 06:53.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TREVOR FULLER: Well, Charlotte
is a welcoming
place, and we like to deal with
our issues

06:53.380 --> 06:59.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by talking through them, by
developing plans
of action together.

06:59.119 --> 07:02.956 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we are not a community that
has this kind
of disruption.

07:02.989 --> 07:08.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are a peaceful community, and
we believe
it's better when we are able to
talk with

07:08.094 --> 07:13.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
each other, even if we have
difficult conversations,
that it's better to talk through
these things

07:13.066 --> 07:17.304 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and develop a communal plan of
action.

07:17.337 --> 07:24.577 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so to have these kinds of
unrest and violence
in our community is something
that is just

07:24.611 --> 07:26.479 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
not normal for us.

07:26.513 --> 07:33.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But do you see
the justification
that apparently many feel for
being angry,

07:33.853 --> 07:44.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
