challenge
systems that hold people back.

21:14.173 --> 21:19.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when black people win, when
black people
succeed in this country, it's
oftentimes been

21:19.211 --> 21:21.780 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a symbol of everyone succeeding.

21:21.814 --> 21:28.120 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And so, as there's been
challenges, black
folks have oftentimes been the
canary in the

21:28.154 --> 21:30.022 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
mine.

21:30.055 --> 21:34.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So what we're seeing in the
streets, this
struggles, the issues around
sort of generational

21:34.660 --> 21:38.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
poverty, they're not just
impacting black
folks, but there is this idea
that we oftentimes

21:38.697 --> 21:43.969 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
say is that, when America gets
the cold, black
people oftentimes get the flu.

21:44.003 --> 21:47.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Vanessa De Luca, on
the cover
of your magazine this month,
there is a striking

21:47.239 --> 21:51.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
photograph of Barack and
Michelle Obama which
looks kind of like a farewell
from the black

21:51.777 --> 21:54.680 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
community to the first black
president and
first lady.

21:54.713 --> 22:00.419 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I wonder if -- do your
readers respond
to you with hope or kind of
despair?

22:00.452 --> 22:09.261 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
VANESSA DE LUCA: Well,
certainly, there is
this kind of longing and wanting
for the Obama

22:09.295 --> 22:13.599 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
administration and the Obama era
to last longer,
without a doubt.

22:13.632 --> 22:19.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there is hope that, in the
next -- whoever
that next administration is,
that they will

22:19.672 --> 22:26.545 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
be cognizant of what is
important to us, that
they will try to address some of
the issues.

22:26.579 --> 22:31.884 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we will hear more about that
at the presidential
debate on Monday.

22:31.917 --> 22:37.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Really, what do they stand for
and what don't
they not stand for in terms of
what resonates

22:38.023 --> 22:40.759 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with our black community?

22:40.793 --> 22:43.529 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's what I think people
are kind of
hopeful for.

22:43.562 --> 22:50.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We just want to hear a word, and
a word that
makes sense for everything
that's going on

22:50.035 --> 22:53.138 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
around us that speaks to how
we're going to
move forward.

22:53.172 --> 22:57.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Andre Perry, what's
a leader's
responsibility in this, whether
it's a president

22:57.610 --> 23:03.382 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or a county commissioner like
who we talked
to earlier, Trevor Fuller, or --
and why should

23:03.415 --> 23:05.751 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it matter at all to the broader
community?

23:05.784 --> 23:09.321 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDRE PERRY: Well, it's not too
much to demand
that we're not shot dead in the
street.

23:09.355 --> 23:13.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's not too much for us to
demand that we
get clean water in Michigan.

23:13.892 --> 23:17.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Some of the things that we are
asking for
are basic human rights.

23:17.630 --> 23:24.036 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so when I look out at the
presidential
landscape, it's not our job just
to anoint

23:24.069 --> 23:28.707 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hillary or Trump, just because
one is a Democrat
or Republican.

23:28.741 --> 23:34.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We really have to charge them
with having
an explicit agenda for black
people.

23:34.380 --> 23:36.282 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so it's not about hope for
me.

23:36.315 --> 23:42.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's about who's going to
deliver the political
goods that we have yet to see
thus far, and

23:42.121 --> 23:45.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
certainly since the Obama
administration and
beyond.

23:45.924 --> 23:50.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Well, let me ask you
all to take
a huge step backward and talk
about perception.

23:50.863 --> 23:56.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We saw in the helicopter footage
of what happened
in Tulsa this week one of the
police officers

23:56.969 --> 24:02.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very far off the ground look at
the man, Terence
Crutcher, who was later killed
and call him

24:02.508 --> 24:04.276 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a bad dude.

24:04.310 --> 24:09.315 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Clearly, there were some
preconceptions, Rashad
Robinson, some idea, even from a
distance,

24:09.348 --> 24:12.151 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that this person must be a
criminal.

24:12.184 --> 24:16.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Are perceptions as much a part
of the problem
here as reality?

24:16.722 --> 24:18.991 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RASHAD ROBINSON: It absolutely
is.

24:19.024 --> 24:23.262 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's absolutely about the
culture, the sort
of daily hostile environment.

24:23.295 --> 24:28.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's not just simply about
getting a job,
right, or being treated fairly
in a hospital,

24:28.334 --> 24:30.736 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but it's about being able to
rent a room.

24:30.769 --> 24:35.774 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I also want to put on the
table that it
just wasn't what the helicopter
-- what they

24:35.808 --> 24:40.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
said in the helicopter about him
being a bad
guy, but it was after he was
shot and laying

24:40.679 --> 24:45.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the ground, and no one rushed
to give him
medical attention.

24:45.317 --> 24:51.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It speaks to this hostile world
that black
people have to live in, the lack
of humanity.

24:51.323 --> 24:56.562 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, first of all, the lack of
benefit of a
doubt of who he was, and then
the lack of

24:56.595 --> 25:03.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
humanity as he laid on the
ground bleeding,
and medical help to save his
life wasn't sort

25:03.102 --> 25:08.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of a first thing that someone
wanted to do,
speaks to a way in which black
people have

25:08.907 --> 25:12.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to -- the things that black
people have to
contend with every day when we
show up to

25:12.711 --> 25:14.380 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a hospital, when we show up to a
courtroom.

25:14.413 --> 25:16.148 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
VANESSA DE LUCA: Right.

25:16.181 --> 25:18.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Let me ask you
Vanessa De Luca,
so maybe we can end on something
of a hopeful

25:18.851 --> 25:22.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
note, if there is such a thing,
which is,
what do we do about this, other
than have

25:22.821 --> 25:24.890 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
another national dialogue,
another conversation?

25:24.923 --> 25:32.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
VANESSA DE LUCA: Well, I mean, I
think, certainly,
people need to use their vote as
their voice,

25:32.731 --> 25:35.534 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
right, that we fought so hard
for that.

25:35.567 --> 25:40.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the idea that there are some
camps that
are saying that they're not
going to vote

25:40.873 --> 25:44.276 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
at all is just unconscionable.

25:44.309 --> 25:49.214 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We fought too hard to get this
right, and
it really does have an impact.

25:49.248 --> 25:54.620 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I know there is the popular vote
vs. the electoral
vote, but people actually need
to exercise

25:54.653 --> 25:59.224 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their right to vote and to make
sure they
are voting for people who are
serving their

25:59.258 --> 26:01.059 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
best interests.

26:01.093 --> 26:06.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I would say let's still --
let's not pass
that off as something that is
just kind of

26:06.098 --> 26:12.371 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
like a throwaway, but let's
really embrace
and not fritter away what so
many generations

26:12.404 --> 26:14.173 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fought so hard for us to be able
to do.

26:14.206 --> 26:18.143 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Vanessa De Luca,
editor in chief
of "Essence" magazine, Andre
Perry, a writer

26:18.177 --> 26:21.914 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
from New Orleans, Rashad
Robinson of Color
of Change, thank you all.

26:21.947 --> 26:23.182 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RASHAD ROBINSON: Thank you.

26:23.215 --> 26:25.350 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
VANESSA DE LUCA: Thank you.

26:25.384 --> 26:31.523 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ANDRE PERRY: You're welcome.

26:31.557 --> 26:37.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In the race to
the White House,
the candidates are taking
different approaches

26:38.030 --> 26:41.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the final days leading up to
the first
debate.

26:41.500 --> 26:43.402 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
John Yang reports.

26:43.435 --> 26:48.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: This morning, Donald
Trump offered
his take on the unrest that has
gripped Charlotte

26:48.273 --> 26:50.042 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the past two nights.

26:50.075 --> 26:52.845 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
The people who will suffer the
most as a result

26:52.878 --> 27:01.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of these riots are law-abiding
African-American
residents who live in these
communities where

27:01.119 --> 27:03.188 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the crime is so rampant.

27:03.222 --> 27:08.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Drugs are a very, very big
factor in what
you're watching on television at
night.

27:08.961 --> 27:13.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: He said his tough law
and order
agenda, which now includes
backing stop and

27:14.032 --> 27:20.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
