ROBERT CIALDINI: Almost no one
recognizes
that the clouds or the coins had
any impact

50:14.011 --> 50:19.016 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on their behavior, and yet it
did at significant
levels.

50:19.049 --> 50:24.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's the cue that drives you in
the direction
of what seems more important now
because you're

50:24.488 --> 50:26.357 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
focused on it.

50:26.390 --> 50:31.195 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Which is why we
flashed the thinker
at the top of this story, to
pre-suade you

50:31.228 --> 50:35.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to ponder the puzzles we posed
at the outset,
but never answered.

50:35.833 --> 50:39.370 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What was the trick of salesman,
the job seeker,
the pricey consultant?

50:39.403 --> 50:42.773 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ROBERT CIALDINI: In each
instance, they did
something first.

50:42.806 --> 50:46.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Starting with the
salesman who
claimed he'd forgotten something
in his car.

50:46.277 --> 50:50.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: He created a
sense of trust,
because who do you let back into
your house

50:50.881 --> 50:53.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by giving them your key, except
someone you
trust?

50:54.018 --> 50:57.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And that made
people more likely
to buy what he was selling?

50:57.154 --> 51:02.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: Yes, because he
had created
a mind-set in them that they
were dealing

51:02.126 --> 51:03.928 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with a trustworthy character.

51:03.961 --> 51:05.896 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And the guy who got
the jobs?

51:05.930 --> 51:10.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: Before every
interview, he
asked the interviewers, why did
you bring

51:10.234 --> 51:11.735 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
me in today?

51:11.769 --> 51:16.507 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
What was it about my
qualifications that made
you attracted to my candidacy?

51:16.540 --> 51:18.275 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And what does that
do?

51:18.309 --> 51:22.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: It caused
people to start
focusing on the positive aspects
of his case

51:22.513 --> 51:24.748 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
before they even began
discussing it.

51:24.782 --> 51:27.318 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And the consultant
who never
got pushback on his fees?

51:27.351 --> 51:32.856 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: He would show
prospects his
proposal and his $75,000 fee.

51:32.890 --> 51:37.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he would say, as you can
tell, I won't
be able to charge you $1 million
for this.

51:37.328 --> 51:38.963 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And what does that
do?

51:38.996 --> 51:44.001 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: Compared to $1
million, $75,000
now seems trivial.

51:44.034 --> 51:48.105 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: And why did
Cialdini urge us
to lead this story with puzzles?

51:48.138 --> 51:55.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: One way to get
pre-suasive
attention to your case is to
begin with a

51:55.446 --> 51:57.314 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
mystery story.

51:57.348 --> 52:04.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mysteries cause people to want
to understand,
to get closure, which caused
them, I hope,

52:04.855 --> 52:08.325 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to want to stay with the
programming and listen
until the end.

52:08.359 --> 52:09.893 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: So, read my palm.

52:09.927 --> 52:12.629 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: Paul, I can see
that you
are a stubborn man.

52:12.663 --> 52:14.565 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: I'm somewhat
stubborn.

52:14.598 --> 52:17.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: What I have
done is to send
you down a memory track where
you would encounter

52:17.801 --> 52:19.203 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
times where you were stubborn.

52:19.236 --> 52:21.372 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And you would look at me and
say, that's right.

52:21.405 --> 52:22.873 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And that's the
whole deal?

52:22.906 --> 52:24.708 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT CIALDINI: No.

52:24.742 --> 52:27.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Suppose I looked at your palm
and saw the
same thing, but said, you're a
very flexible

52:27.244 --> 52:29.146 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
man.

52:29.179 --> 52:32.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now I have sent you down a
memory track where
you would encounter times where
you were flexible,

52:32.149 --> 52:33.984 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and you would say to me, that's
right.

52:34.018 --> 52:35.786 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's who I am.

52:35.819 --> 52:38.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Well, I might not
be quite that
histrionic, but I think I would
say, yes,

52:38.422 --> 52:40.190 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm flexible.

52:40.224 --> 52:43.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: And I have even
done that
with a person at a party, read
his palm, told

52:43.961 --> 52:48.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
