beginning, told
him that he was a flexible guy
at the end,

52:48.432 --> 52:50.501 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and he said "You're right" both
times.

52:50.534 --> 52:55.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: But, hey, Making
Sense is supposed
to be the "NewsHour"'s weekly
economics segment.

52:55.906 --> 53:02.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, economics, as it's taught
and practiced,
is based on the notion of
rational maximization.

53:02.279 --> 53:03.981 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ROBERT CIALDINI: Correct.

53:04.014 --> 53:06.950 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: This is not
rational maximization.

53:06.984 --> 53:08.752 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT CIALDINI: No.

53:08.786 --> 53:14.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What new psychology suggests,
it's the factor
that is top of consciousness at
the moment

53:14.758 --> 53:18.796 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
